details.description: The Book Lady of Monroe specializes in used books. Walking into the store is a bit like stepping into Narnia’s Wardrobe or Dr. Who’s Tardis … there is so much more than is apparent from the outside. You can enjoy settling in one of the several cozy sitting corners to visit or read a while. Carol Gordon, The Book Lady, has made sure to fill every nook and cranny of her 3,900 square feet with a fantastic selection. From our exceptional children’s section and every genre of fiction and nonfiction including Christian, history, biography, art, science, home, gardening, health, crafts, cookbooks and more, The Book Lady of Monroe has it all. So stop in and browse, take a peek around the corner.

reviews_data.review_text: Always a good place to be. If you love books you could get lost for hours . Of course that’s easier if you have zero distractions like the list of things you must get done today. But really it is a wonderful place to be.

The absolute best place to go if you’re a reader,or have kids looking for affordable books. Got books to donate? They’ll give you store credit for your gently used books. They have everything you can possibly imagine. The place is well organized.  It’s easy to find what you are looking for, or if you prefer, spend the whole day browsing.  It’s an Amazing place.  Great for new teachers who need to build their classroom library.
Love this store! They have so many options.  They make it easy to get lost in the magical world of books.
Awesome people and great prices. Ask for Aimee and tell her Victor sent you. 🤗

Our visit to The Book Lady in Monroe turned an ordinary Saturday into a delightful one.

As avid readers, we were pleasantly surprised to find rows upon rows of books neatly organized by genre. From fiction and self-help to non-fiction and more, the selection was broad and thoughtfully curated. There’s even a dedicated section for Christian literature, if that’s your interest.

One highlight for me was the collection of vintage science magazines—charming pieces that covered fascinating topics from years past. Their classics section also stood out. Prices across the store were quite reasonable, which made browsing even more enjoyable.

The staff were kind and helpful, and there’s a restroom conveniently located at the back. Plus, the clever feline references scattered throughout the store added a playful touch that had us smiling.

There’s ample parking outside, and all in all, The Book Lady is a gem of a bookstore that’s sure to delight the reader in you.
Great selection and service

AMAZING store! Such great selections and prices!!!
Obsessed! If you are obsessed with books you will be obsessed with it!!!

My daughter and I love The Book Lady! A fantastic used bookstore with a great selection of books of all sorts and a wonderful staff. Their children's, middle grades, and YA sections are particularly large. They often have signings by local authors as well!

This place is lovely! The people there were so kind and helpful! It's fairly priced and you can get lost in the stacks. There's fun signs and things on the top shelves that make exploring even more fun. A wonderful place!

Be very cautious selling here and accumulating any store credit. They have a history of changing the trade/sell policies to better benefit themselves after they take your stuff. They will NO LONGER honor the policies that were in place when they accepted your items. New policy changes aren’t just going forward on new trades as you’d expect, they magically apply to all previous trade credits too. Who does this??? I’ve got lots of credit here but now you must be willing to spend 50% cash on every purchase to be able to use any of it. I would have never brought in items under those policies. It used to be a small percentage of cash (20%) but it has crept up over the years. Now I would have to spent $100 of money just to be able to use my $100 of store credit. This is a really shady business practice. Change policies all you want but it needs to be going forward. You shouldn’t be able to change the agreement to benefit yourself once you’ve already completed a transaction and taken someone’s books. You certainly wouldn’t let me demand more money for my books now,
why can the business? I would have never taken books in under the current trade policies. Can only wonder how many other people this has happened to? How much money owed other people for trades is also being held hostage to keep a positive cash flow running through this business. Other used book business may waste your time (2 nd & C) on the front side by giving you basically nothing for your trade but this place does business with you then changes their policies and is able to then hold your credit hostage. They already have taken your books and maybe even sold them but you can’t access any of your credit you’re owed unless you spend more and eventually more money. They won’t agree to pay you out what they owe you either. Just how much money DOES the store owe people on all those little cards they keep track of everything on????  A LOT! So shady.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Dear Family Traveler.  This is Carol Gordon the Owner of the Book Lady of Monroe.  My independent used bookstore has been in business in Monroe for 37 years.  We offer gently used books at competitive prices further discounted by trade credit which never expires.  We did change the trade credit percentages in 2020 due to economic necessity.  We did post the upcoming change for months before we put it into effect.  You have repeated the same message about the change multiple times during the last five years.  I have asked you to contact me in the interest of putting your issue to rest.  You have not done so.  I am sorry that you do not like our current trade policy.  My trade policy is most fair and is what is needed to keep our store in business.  Please know that we appreciate all our customers.

reviews_data.review_text: Best place to go for used books at great prices !!

A Monroe staple and I can’t believe this was my first time in. It’s a lot bigger than I had imagined. There aren’t many new books but the selection of used books is unmatched. Absolutely lovely, make sure you’ve got some time set aside to browse and sift through lots and lots of shelves!

I walked into the bookstore because I’m an avid reader and live right across the street. The sign on the door asked that customers use the sanitizer on the front counter, so I did so after walking inside. At least three employees looked at me without a greeting. However, two individuals who were donating books came in after me and they were given a warm welcome. I proceeded to browse the selection for about five minutes or so.  During this time, no one asked if I needed help finding anything, but I heard them asking other customers if they needed assistance.

While I hate to be that person I do want to note that I was the only person of color in the shop at that time and felt like I was being ignored simply because of that. I don’t like to think that way but I’m simply unable to fathom any other reason why I wasn’t shown the same level of customer service as others. This was a very unpleasant experience and I won’t be back.
Fantastic place. Great selection of books!

A lovely and cozy bookshop with so much to explore! They trade books as well as sell them, and no matter what type of books you like, you are bound to find something good while you are here. The owner is such a sweetheart and I'm glad she runs such a wonderful store!

Love the vibe of this place it's a very calm and peaceful place to enjoy going through books or even trading in books love this place truly great vibes

This is hands down my favorite used bookstore in Charlotte. The selection is fantastic, and the shelves are always well-organized. I’ve been filling my daughter’s bookshelf from here for seven years! They also have puzzles—one of the few places I’ve found to pick up great quality used puzzles. I enjoy the trade-in system, too, where you can bring in books and get partial credit toward purchases—it’s such a nice perk. I recently heard a rumor that the store might be closing, so I stopped in to check, and I’m happy to confirm that it’s NOT true. It's definitely worth a visit no matter where you love in the area,. Justgive yourself twice the time you "think" you need!

raw_data.description: The Book Lady of Monroe specializes in used books. Walking into the store is a bit like stepping into Narnia’s Wardrobe or Dr. Who’s Tardis … there is so much more than is apparent from the outside. You can enjoy settling in one of the several cozy sitting corners to visit or read a while. Carol Gordon, The Book Lady, has made sure to fill every nook and cranny of her 3,900 square feet with a fantastic selection. From our exceptional children’s section and every genre of fiction and nonfiction including Christian, history, biography, art, science, home, gardening, health, crafts, cookbooks and more, The Book Lady of Monroe has it all. So stop in and browse, take a peek around the corner.

reviews_data.review_text: Always a good place to be. If you love books you could get lost for hours . Of course that’s easier if you have zero distractions like the list of things you must get done today. But really it is a wonderful place to be.

The absolute best place to go if you’re a reader,or have kids looking for affordable books. Got books to donate? They’ll give you store credit for your gently used books. They have everything you can possibly imagine. The place is well organized.  It’s easy to find what you are looking for, or if you prefer, spend the whole day browsing.  It’s an Amazing place.  Great for new teachers who need to build their classroom library.
Love this store! They have so many options.  They make it easy to get lost in the magical world of books.

Our visit to The Book Lady in Monroe turned an ordinary Saturday into a delightful one.

As avid readers, we were pleasantly surprised to find rows upon rows of books neatly organized by genre. From fiction and self-help to non-fiction and more, the selection was broad and thoughtfully curated. There’s even a dedicated section for Christian literature, if that’s your interest.

One highlight for me was the collection of vintage science magazines—charming pieces that covered fascinating topics from years past. Their classics section also stood out. Prices across the store were quite reasonable, which made browsing even more enjoyable.

The staff were kind and helpful, and there’s a restroom conveniently located at the back. Plus, the clever feline references scattered throughout the store added a playful touch that had us smiling.

There’s ample parking outside, and all in all, The Book Lady is a gem of a bookstore that’s sure to delight the reader in you.

Be very cautious selling here and accumulating any store credit. They have a history of changing the trade/sell policies to better benefit themselves after they take your stuff. They will NO LONGER honor the policies that were in place when they accepted your items. New policy changes aren’t just going forward on new trades as you’d expect, they magically apply to all previous trade credits too. Who does this??? I’ve got lots of credit here but now you must be willing to spend 50% cash on every purchase to be able to use any of it. I would have never brought in items under those policies. It used to be a small percentage of cash (20%) but it has crept up over the years. Now I would have to spent $100 of money just to be able to use my $100 of store credit. This is a really shady business practice. Change policies all you want but it needs to be going forward. You shouldn’t be able to change the agreement to benefit yourself once you’ve already completed a transaction and taken someone’s books. You certainly wouldn’t let me demand more money for my books now,
why can the business? I would have never taken books in under the current trade policies. Can only wonder how many other people this has happened to? How much money owed other people for trades is also being held hostage to keep a positive cash flow running through this business. Other used book business may waste your time (2 nd & C) on the front side by giving you basically nothing for your trade but this place does business with you then changes their policies and is able to then hold your credit hostage. They already have taken your books and maybe even sold them but you can’t access any of your credit you’re owed unless you spend more and eventually more money. They won’t agree to pay you out what they owe you either. Just how much money DOES the store owe people on all those little cards they keep track of everything on????  A LOT! So shady.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Dear Family Traveler.  This is Carol Gordon the Owner of the Book Lady of Monroe.  My independent used bookstore has been in business in Monroe for 37 years.  We offer gently used books at competitive prices further discounted by trade credit which never expires.  We did change the trade credit percentages in 2020 due to economic necessity.  We did post the upcoming change for months before we put it into effect.  You have repeated the same message about the change multiple times during the last five years.  I have asked you to contact me in the interest of putting your issue to rest.  You have not done so.  I am sorry that you do not like our current trade policy.  My trade policy is most fair and is what is needed to keep our store in business.  Please know that we appreciate all our customers.

I walked into the bookstore because I’m an avid reader and live right across the street. The sign on the door asked that customers use the sanitizer on the front counter, so I did so after walking inside. At least three employees looked at me without a greeting. However, two individuals who were donating books came in after me and they were given a warm welcome. I proceeded to browse the selection for about five minutes or so.  During this time, no one asked if I needed help finding anything, but I heard them asking other customers if they needed assistance.

While I hate to be that person I do want to note that I was the only person of color in the shop at that time and felt like I was being ignored simply because of that. I don’t like to think that way but I’m simply unable to fathom any other reason why I wasn’t shown the same level of customer service as others. This was a very unpleasant experience and I won’t be back.

raw_data.description: The Book Lady of Monroe specializes in used books. Walking into the store is a bit like stepping into Narnia’s Wardrobe or Dr. Who’s Tardis … there is so much more than is apparent from the outside. You can enjoy settling in one of the several cozy sitting corners to visit or read a while. Carol Gordon, The Book Lady, has made sure to fill every nook and cranny of her 3,900 square feet with a fantastic selection. From our exceptional children’s section and every genre of fiction and nonfiction including Christian, history, biography, art, science, home, gardening, health, crafts, cookbooks and more, The Book Lady of Monroe has it all. So stop in and browse, take a peek around the corner.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend 15 min to 1.5 hr here
